For testing at the command line:

    1. make copy of layman.cfg-template
    2. export LAYMAN_CFG env variable
    3. make copy of layman.py-template
    4. run python layman.py

    Alternative way:

    1. leave it as it is (if you know, defaults.cfg containtes proper values)
    2. run python layman.py-template

    You can now access the service from

        http://localhost:8080/layman/

For running on the server:

    1. configure layman.cfg and layman.py to your needs
    2. make link from cgi-bin to layman.py, e.g.:
        
        ln -s ./layman.py /usr/lib/cgi-bin/layman.py

    3. You can now access the service directly from

        http://localhost/cgi-bin/layman.py/layman/

For using the test suite
    
    1. Change directory to tests

        cd tests

    2. run layman.py

        python layman.py

    3. In case, only particular test suite is needed, pickup one file and use it

        python fileman.py

